name: AzureAcr
help: Manage private registries with Azure Container Registries.

properties.name: Registry
properties.help: The name of the container registry. You can configure the default registry name using `az configure --defaults acr=&lt;registry name&gt;`.

properties.name: AuthMode
properties.help: Auth mode of the source registry.

properties.name: BuildArg
properties.help: Build argument in '--build-arg name[=value]' format. Multiples supported by passing --build-arg multiple times.

properties.name: File
properties.help: The relative path of the the docker file to the source code root folder. Default to 'Dockerfile'.

properties.name: Image
properties.help: The name and tag of the image using the format: '-t repo/image:tag'. Multiple tags are supported by passing -t multiple times.

properties.name: NoFormat
properties.help: Indicates whether the logs should be displayed in raw format.

properties.name: NoLogs
properties.help: Do not show logs after successfully queuing the build.

properties.name: NoPush
properties.help: Indicates whether the image built should be pushed to the registry.

properties.name: NoWait
properties.help: Do not wait for the build to complete and return immediately after queuing the build.

properties.name: Platform
properties.help: The platform where build/task is run, Eg, 'windows' and 'linux'. When it's used in build commands, it also can be specified in 'os/arch/variant' format for the resulting image. Eg, linux/arm/v7. The 'arch' and 'variant' parts are optional.

properties.name: ResourceGroup
properties.help: Name of resource group. You can configure the default group using `az configure --defaults group=&lt;name&gt;`.

properties.name: SecretBuildArg
properties.help: Secret build argument in '--secret-build-arg name[=value]' format. Multiples supported by passing '--secret-build-arg name[=value]' multiple times.

properties.name: Target
properties.help: The name of the target build stage.

properties.name: Timeout
properties.help: The timeout in seconds.

properties.name: Subscription
properties.help: Name or ID of subscription. You can configure the default subscription using `az account set -s NAME_OR_ID`.

properties.name: IgnoreErrors
properties.help: Ignore errors, displaying them only at the final.
